    <h1>Circle of Voices</h1>
    <h2>a multimedia journey among Quebec First Nations*</h2>

      <h5>This website presents an anthropological research project conducted in the summer of 2016 in Quebec region.
   Merging digital tools and collaborative methodologies, I worked in depth with the *atikamekw, abenakis and
   wolastoqiyik Nations, in particular with <a href="the-women">six young women</a>. This project aims first to
   bring educational awareness about the situation of Native youth, in particular women. It also wishes to serve
   as a platform to uphold the defense of their rights by linking the movements of resurgence and self-determination.
   You can find more about the academic writing and the researcher in the about section.
</h5>

